headline: What Walt Disney (DIS)'s Ticket Price Hike and Leadership Moves Mean for Shareholders
summary: In late September 2025, The Walt Disney Company extended the employment agreement of Sonia L. Coleman through June 2028, promoting her to Senior Executive Vice President and Chief People Officer, while also announcing significant ticket price increases at Disneyland and Disney World, with one-day tickets surpassing US$200 for the first time. This combination of heightened pricing and executive leadership shifts has sparked fresh questions among analysts regarding consumer demand health and...
